Package pingball.physics

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Absorber
    An Absorber is a type of Gadget that has a variable size.
    Ball
    A Ball is a computerized model of a physical, impenetrable ball that will bounce around in a pingball game (a computerized version of pinball).
    Board
    A board represents the playing area for a game of Pingball.
    CircleBumper
    CircleBumper is a type of Gadget that can exist in Pingball.
    Flipper
    A Flipper is a movable Gadget that can hit a ball.
    Gadget
    A Gadget represents anything that can be placed on a Pingball board.
    OuterWalls
    OuterWalls is a special type of Gadget that is used to monitor reflections of balls off of the outer boundaries of the playing field.
    SquareBumper
    SquareBumper is a type of Gadget that can exist in Pingball.
    TriangularBumper
    TriangularBumper is a type of Gadget that can exist in Pingball.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Orientation
    Defines a set of orientations that objects can be in as specified for pingball.
